            "actions": {
                "create": [],
                "call": [
                    "NoOp"
                ]
            },
            "readonly": false,
            "desc": "Owner-only method to register the Escrow application ID.\nCalled once after Escrow is deployed to establish the approved caller. Only the Escrow contract can then call record_fee_collected.",
            "events": [
                {
                    "name": "EscrowAppSet",
                    "args": [
                        {
                            "type": "uint64",
                            "name": "field1"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "recommendations": {}
        },
        {
            "name": "record_fee_collected",
            "args": [
                {
                    "type": "uint64",
                    "name": "fee_amount_micro_usdc",
                    "desc": "Fee amount in microUSDC to add to running total"
                }
            ],
            "returns": {
                "type": "void"
            },
            "actions": {
                "create": [],
                "call": [
                    "NoOp"
                ]
            },
            "readonly": false,
            "desc": "Records collected fee amount to the running total.\nCalled by Escrow after successful fee transfer to update total_fees_collected.\nCaller Guard: Only the Escrow contract (identified by escrow_app_id) may call this. This prevents unauthorized callers from inflating the revenue counter.\nImplementation: Checks that either: 1. Caller is the current application (self-call), OR 2. Caller app ID matches registered escrow_app_id",
            "events": [
                {
                    "name": "FeeCollected",
                    "args": [
                        {
                            "type": "uint64",
                            "name": "field1"
                        },
                        {
                            "type": "uint64",
                            "name": "field2"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "recommendations": {}
        },
        {
            "name": "get_config",
            "args": [],
            "returns": {
                "type": "(uint64,address,uint64,uint64)",
                "desc": "Tuple of (fee_rate_bps, treasury_address, total_fees_collected, usdc_asset_id)"
            },
            "actions": {
                "create": [],
                "call": [
                    "NoOp"
                ]
            },
            "readonly": true,
            "desc": "Returns current FeeConfig state for Operations dashboard.\nCalled frequently (e.g., every 10 seconds) to display: - Current fee rate - Treasury address - Cumulative fees collected (platform revenue to date) - USDC asset ID (confirms network)",
            "events": [],
            "recommendations": {}
        }
    ],
    "arcs": [
        22,
        28
    ],
    "desc": "\n    FeeConfig contract manages USDC fee collection for the Mercator insight marketplace.\n    \n    Stores:\n    - owner: deployer address (only wallet allowed to update fee parameters)\n    - fee_rate_bps: fee rate in basis points (1 bps = 0.01%, range 0-1000)\n    - treasury_address: wallet receiving all collected fees\n    - total_fees_collected: running total of fees collected in microUSDC\n    - usdc_asset_id: USDC ASA ID (TestNet=10458941, MainNet=31566704)\n    \n    Methods:\n    - calculate_fee: pure read-only; returns fee with 1 microUSDC minimum for non-zero amounts\n    - calculate_seller_payout: convenience method returning amount - fee\n    - set_fee_rate: owner-only; validates rate <= 1000 (10% hard cap)\n    - set_treasury: owner-only; updates treasury address\n    - get_config: returns current fee_rate_bps, treasury_address, total_fees_collected, usdc_asset_id\n    ",
